Program: Outlook
Title: Frank Sinatra's Australian Showdown
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswt6x
Last Broadcast Date: Christmas Eve 2018
In 1974, Australian concert producer Robert Raymond got the gig of his life – organising the comeback tour of his musical idol, Frank Sinatra. The anticipation in Australia was huge and the tour sold-out immediately. But when his opening night performance caused a scandal, Sinatra found himself caught in a stand-off… and Robert Raymond had the biggest test of his career – how to get Sinatra back on stage? Presenter: Emily Webb Producer: Maryam Maruf and Tom Roseingrave Image: Frank Sinatra Credit: Jay Dickman/CORBIS/Getty Images Show less